---
// src/components/FaqAccordion.astro
interface Props {
    title?: string;
    titleClass?: string;
    isReleased?: boolean;
}

const { 
    title = "Frequently Asked Questions", 
    titleClass = "text-3xl font-medium text-center text-primary mb-8",
    isReleased = false
} = Astro.props;
---

<h2 class={titleClass}>
    {title}
</h2>
<div class="space-y-4">
    <details
        class="group bg-card rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 shadow-lg shadow-black/5 dark:shadow-none transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:border-brand-accent/50 hover:shadow-brand-glow"
    >
        <summary
            class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none p-6"
        >
            <span class="font-medium text-primary"
                >What is LatteArtist, and how can it help me improve my latte
                art?</span
            >
            <span
                class="text-secondary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200"
            >
                <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    class="h-5 w-5"
                    viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                    fill="currentColor"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                >
                    <path
                        fill-rule="evenodd"
                        d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z"
                        clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                </svg>
            </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6">
            <p class="mt-3 text-secondary">
                I designed LatteArtist as an iOS app specifically for
                <strong>home baristas</strong> and coffee enthusiasts like myself
                who want to <strong>track their latte art progress</strong> and
                <strong>consistently improve their skills</strong>. With
                LatteArtist, I aim to help you:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 text-secondary list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                <li>
                    <strong>Log every pour:</strong> Easily capture photos and details
                    of your <strong>latte art</strong>, including
                    <strong>pattern type</strong> (like <strong>hearts</strong> or
                    <strong>tulips</strong>), <strong>milk used</strong> (even
                    <strong>oat milk</strong> and other <strong
                        >alt milks</strong
                    >), <strong>cup size</strong>, and notes on your technique.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Understand what works:</strong> By logging key details
                    about each <strong>pour</strong>, such as the
                    <strong>milk you used</strong>, the
                    <strong>pattern you attempted</strong>, and any notes on
                    your technique, you can start to see what impacts your
                    results and learn how to <strong>troubleshoot</strong> common
                    issues like "<strong>jaggy hearts</strong>."
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Visualize your journey:</strong> See your
                    <strong>progression</strong> over time with a visual
                    <strong>timeline</strong> and <strong>rate</strong> your pours
                    to objectively assess your improvement.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Stay motivated:</strong> Track your
                    <strong>streaks</strong> and celebrate your successes as you
                    learn to replicate what works and understand your "random good/bad
                    days."
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details
        class="group bg-card rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 shadow-lg shadow-black/5 dark:shadow-none transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:border-brand-accent/50 hover:shadow-brand-glow"
    >
        <summary
            class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none p-6"
        >
            <span class="font-medium text-primary"
                >How does LatteArtist make tracking my espresso and latte art
                pours easy?</span
            >
            <span
                class="text-secondary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200"
            >
                <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    class="h-5 w-5"
                    viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                    fill="currentColor"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                >
                    <path
                        fill-rule="evenodd"
                        d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z"
                        clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                </svg>
            </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6">
            <p class="mt-3 text-secondary">
                I know that <strong>inputting data</strong> can be a hassle, so I've
                designed LatteArtist for speed and minimal friction. You can quickly
                log key <strong>parameters</strong> for each
                <strong>pour</strong>, including photo,
                <strong>pattern type</strong>, <strong>milk details</strong>,
                <strong>cup information</strong>, and your personal
                <strong>rating</strong>. My goal is to make it an intuitive part
                of your <strong>espresso</strong> and
                <strong>latte art workflow</strong>, not a burden, so you can
                focus on improving your <strong>frothing</strong> and pouring.
            </p>
        </div>
    </details>

    {!isReleased && (
        <details
            class="group bg-card rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 shadow-lg shadow-black/5 dark:shadow-none transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:border-brand-accent/50 hover:shadow-brand-glow"
        >
            <summary
                class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none p-6"
            >
                <span class="font-medium text-primary"
                    >When will the LatteArtist app be available for iOS?</span
                >
                <span
                    class="text-secondary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200"
                >
                    <svg
                        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                        class="h-5 w-5"
                        viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                        fill="currentColor"
                        aria-hidden="true"
                    >
                        <path
                            fill-rule="evenodd"
                            d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z"
                            clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                    </svg>
                </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6">
                <p class="mt-3 text-secondary">
                    LatteArtist is currently in private beta for iOS. By signing up
                    for early access, you can join my TestFlight beta program. This
                    is a great opportunity for you to be among the first to use the
                    app, provide <strong>feedback</strong>, and help me shape its
                    development based on real <strong>home barista</strong> needs!
                </p>
            </div>
        </details>
    )}

    <details
        class="group bg-card rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 shadow-lg shadow-black/5 dark:shadow-none transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:border-brand-accent/50 hover:shadow-brand-glow"
    >
        <summary
            class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none p-6"
        >
            <span class="font-medium text-primary"
                >I'm an Android user. Is an Android version of LatteArtist
                planned?</span
            >
            <span
                class="text-secondary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200"
            >
                <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    class="h-5 w-5"
                    viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                    fill="currentColor"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                >
                    <path
                        fill-rule="evenodd"
                        d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z"
                        clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                </svg>
            </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6">
            <p class="mt-3 text-secondary">
                I've heard the interest from Android users! Currently, my
                primary focus is on perfecting the
                <strong>latte art tracking</strong> experience for iOS. An Android
                version is something I'll definitely consider in the future based
                on continued demand and as the app matures.
            </p>
        </div>
    </details>

    {!isReleased && (
        <details
            class="group bg-card rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 shadow-lg shadow-black/5 dark:shadow-none transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:border-brand-accent/50 hover:shadow-brand-glow"
        >
            <summary
                class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none p-6"
            >
                <span class="font-medium text-primary"
                    >How can I provide feedback or suggest ideas?</span
                >
                <span
                    class="text-secondary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200"
                >
                    <svg
                        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                        class="h-5 w-5"
                        viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                        fill="currentColor"
                        aria-hidden="true"
                    >
                        <path
                            fill-rule="evenodd"
                            d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z"
                            clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                    </svg>
                </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6">
                <p class="mt-3 text-secondary">
                    Your <strong>feedback</strong> is invaluable in helping me make LatteArtist
                    the best tool for our
                    <strong>latte art community</strong>! When you sign up, you can
                    reply to the welcome email with your thoughts. Once you're in
                    the beta, you can also provide feedback directly through the
                    TestFlight app. I'm excited to hear your ideas for new features
                    or improvements to the <strong>UI/UX</strong>.
                </p>
            </div>
        </details>
    )}

    <details
        class="group bg-card rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 shadow-lg shadow-black/5 dark:shadow-none transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:border-brand-accent/50 hover:shadow-brand-glow"
    >
        <summary
            class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none p-6"
        >
            <span class="font-medium text-primary"
                >Can LatteArtist help me understand why my latte art is
                inconsistent?</span
            >
            <span
                class="text-secondary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200"
            >
                <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    class="h-5 w-5"
                    viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                    fill="currentColor"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                >
                    <path
                        fill-rule="evenodd"
                        d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z"
                        clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                </svg>
            </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6">
            <p class="mt-3 text-secondary">
                Absolutely! One of my core goals with LatteArtist is to help you
                move beyond "random good/bad days" with your
                <strong>pours</strong>. By consistently logging details like
                your <strong>milk type</strong> (including
                <strong>oat milk</strong> or other alternatives),
                and even
                <strong>cup shape</strong> and <strong>volume</strong>, you can start to identify patterns.
                Reviewing your <strong>timeline</strong> and
                <strong>ratings</strong> alongside these variables can provide insights
                into what leads to successful
                <strong>latte art</strong> and what might be causing inconsistencies.
            </p>
        </div>
    </details>
</div>
